
                                            A 40-year-old man has shot and killed himself and three of his children in Umtata.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A 40-year-old man has shot and killed himself and three of his children in Umtata. It’s understood the man shot the children, aged between one and eight, while their mother was on the same property. The reasons behind the incident are not yet known. The police's Mzukisi Fatyela says an investigation is underway. “We are not sure for the motive behind the killings. The mother of the children was inside the house during the shootings.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)